T*
(perform some possibly slow computation at a latter time in web applications. Basically queues) Tj
T*
(allow to split a computation in two times, the time the computation is scheduled, and the time) Tj
T*
(the computation is executed. A ?producer?, will put a task to be executed into a queue, and a) Tj
T*
(?consumer? or ?worker? will get tasks from the queue to execute them. For example once a new) Tj
T*
(user completes the registration process in a web application, the web application will add a) Tj
T*
(new task to the queue in order to send an email with the activation link. The actual process of) Tj
T*
(sending an email, that may require retrying if there are transient network failures or other) Tj
T*
(errors, is up to the worker. Technically speaking we can think at queues as a form of) Tj
T*
(inter-process messaging primitive, where the receiving process needs to acknowledge the) Tj
T*
(reception of the message. Messages can not be fire-and-forget, since the queue needs to) Tj
T*
(understand if the message can be removed from the queue, so some form of acknowledgement is) Tj
T*
(strictly required. When receiving a message triggers the execution of a task, like it happens) Tj
