(suddenly all the internet needs to be patched. Moreover for me personally how trivial the bug) Tj
T*
(is, is disturbing. I don?t want to point the finger to the OpenSSL developers, but you just) Tj
T*
(usually think at those class of issues as a bit more subtle, in the case of a software like) Tj
T*
(OpenSSL. Usually you fail to do sanity checks *correctly*, as opposed to this bug where there) Tj
T*
(is a total *lack* of bound checks in the memcpy\(\) call. However sometimes in the morning I read) Tj
T*
(the code I wrote the night before and I?m deeply embarrassed. Programmers sometimes fail, I for) Tj
T*
(sure do often, so my guess is that what is needed is a different process, and not a different) Tj
T*
(OpenSSL team. There is who proposes a different language safer than C, and who proposes that) Tj
T*
(the specification is broken because it is too complex. Probably there is some truth in both) Tj
T*
(arguments, however it is unlikely that we move to a different specification or system language) Tj
T*
(soon, so the real question is, what we can do now to improve system software security? 1\) Throw) Tj
T*
(money at it. Making system code safer is simple if there are investments. If...) Tj
T*
() Tj
