(I enjoy reading a lot of source code and after 15 years in the field I feel like I have seen my) Tj
T*
(fair share. Even with a full-time job, I still try to spare evenings here and there to read. I) Tj
T*
(don't see myself every stopping. It is always an opportunity to learn new things to follow) Tj
T*
(somebody's mind process. Every once in a while I come across a solution to a problem that is so) Tj
T*
(elegant, and so creative that there is no other word but "beautiful" to describe it. Q_rsqrt,) Tj
T*
(better knows as "Inverse Square Root" and popularized by Quake 3, definitely belong to the) Tj
T*
(family of breathtaking wizardry. While I was working on the Game Engine Black Book: Wolfenstein) Tj
T*
(3D I came across an other one: Fizzlefade. Fizzlefade is the name of the function in charge of) Tj
T*
(fading from a scene to an other in Wolfenstein 3D. What it does is turn the pixels of the) Tj
T*
(screen to a solid color, only one at a time, seemingly at random. More...) Tj
T*
() Tj
